ARTICLE 1 — DEFINITIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1.1  "Licensor" means Korlu Solutions Digitales inc. and its successors.

1.2  "Covered Work" means exclusively the original work authored, created, or
     contributed by or on behalf of Korlu Solutions Digitales inc., including
     but not limited to:
       (a) custom source code written by or for Licensor;
       (b) configuration files, scripts, and automation authored by Licensor;
       (c) infrastructure definitions, deployment manifests, and orchestration
           files created by Licensor;
       (d) integration logic, business processes, and workflows designed by
           Licensor;
       (e) modifications, customizations, and adaptations applied by Licensor
           to Third-Party Software (as defined in Article 1.4);
       (f) documentation, architecture designs, and technical specifications
           authored by Licensor.

1.3  "Authorized Contributor" means any natural person or automated tool
     (including but not limited to artificial intelligence assistants, code
     analysis tools, and automated scanners) that accesses or modifies the
     Covered Work exclusively under one of the following conditions:
       (a) the person is a current employee of Korlu Solutions Digitales inc.
           acting within the scope of their employment;
       (b) the person is an officer or director of Korlu Solutions Digitales
           inc.;
       (c) the person or entity has been expressly mandated in writing by Korlu
           Solutions Digitales inc. to perform work on its behalf (including
           contractors, consultants, and mandated service providers);
       (d) the automated tool is operated exclusively by and under the direct
           control of a person described in (a), (b), or (c) above.

1.4  "Third-Party Software" means any software, framework, library, tool,
     application, or component that was developed independently by parties
     other than Licensor, regardless of whether it is open source, freeware,
     or commercially licensed. Third-Party Software includes, without
     limitation, open source projects, operating systems, container runtimes,
     orchestration platforms, databases, messaging systems, and monitoring
     tools incorporated or referenced within this repository.

1.5  "Licensee" means any individual or entity that accesses, downloads,
     copies, or uses the Covered Work, other than an Authorized Contributor
     acting within the scope of their mandate.

