ARTICLE 3 — AUTHORIZED CONTRIBUTORS — RIGHT TO MODIFY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3.1  EXCLUSIVE RIGHT TO MODIFY. Only Authorized Contributors, as defined in
     Article 1.3, have the right to access, modify, commit, deploy, or
     otherwise alter the Covered Work. Any access to or modification of the
     Covered Work by any person or entity that does not qualify as an
     Authorized Contributor is strictly prohibited and constitutes an
     infringement of Licensor's rights.

3.2  AUTOMATED TOOLS. The use of automated tools, including artificial
     intelligence assistants, code generation systems, code scanning tools,
     static analysis tools, and similar systems, is permitted solely when such
     tools are operated by and under the direct control of an Authorized
     Contributor acting within the scope of their mandate from Korlu Solutions
     Digitales inc. The use of such tools by any other party on the Covered
     Work is strictly prohibited.

3.3  CONTRIBUTIONS BECOME PROPERTY OF LICENSOR. Any modification, addition,
     or contribution made to the Covered Work by an Authorized Contributor in
     the course of their employment or mandate shall automatically become the
     exclusive property of Korlu Solutions Digitales inc. upon creation,
     without further act or assignment, to the fullest extent permitted by
     applicable law.

3.4  END OF MANDATE. Upon termination of employment, contract, or mandate,
     an Authorized Contributor's right to access or modify the Covered Work
     immediately and automatically ceases. All copies in the former Authorized
     Contributor's possession must be returned or destroyed.

